{
  "narration": "You are standing on the tip of a giant battleaxe, its blade resting against a huge wall of canvas. The shaft is as wide as a sidewalk, sloping downward into dimness. A faint luminescence emanates from the canvas walls — some side effect of the bag's magic. Above, barely above head height, the canvas forms a low ceiling, scrunching shut in the centre. The top of the blade has made a small rip in the fabric. If you balance carefully on the tip, you could poke your head through. You can drop down into the darkness below, or clamber carefully down the axe handle.",
  "npc_response": null,
  "knowledge_tags": null,
  "attitude_changes": null
}

{
  "narration": "You steady yourself on the battleaxe's tip, your heart hammering as you stretch upward toward the small rip in the canvas. The fabric squeaks under your fingers but holds firm. Carefully, you pull yourself up and poke your head through the gap. Beyond is a grey, infinite void – the Astral Plane. It's cold and silent, with a faint pressure like being underwater. Peeking around, you can see the exterior of the Bag of Holding, a bulging sack of rough canvas. A giant padlock dangles from the cinched neck, barely within reach from this precarious perch. It's firmly locked, but perhaps you could feel it for keyholes or tamper with it if you could get a hand on it. For now, you're just head and shoulders through the rip – the rest of you remains perched on the axe blade.",
  "npc_response": null,
  "knowledge_tags": null,
  "attitude_changes": null
}
